MISS MY BROTHER<br>
Mon May 26 10:00:32 US/Eastern 1997 <br><br>
May 26, 1997<br><br>
Today is Memorial Day and, as always, my thoughts turn to my brother, Don McKenzie, who was killed in Vietnam on December 10, 1968 in Cou Chi. He was just a boy, only 22 years old, and the sweetest, kindest person in the world. My life hasn't been the same since he died and although it's been almost 29 years I still miss him and think about him every day, and love him very much. When people ask me if I have brothers and sisters I always say I have a younger sister and don't mention Don until I get to know them--it's still too painful. I don't think I will ever get over his death and I don't think I will ever have back that piece of my heart that died on December 10, 1968. <br><br>
-- Graham@poe.coe.ncsu.edu (Susan McKenzie Graham) <br><br>
